From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dimitris Panokostas <midwan@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] uae: flush JIT translation blocks synchronously on reset

Frode's original qemu-uae plugin and the QEMU 9.2.4 build flush the PPC
translation block cache synchronously in ppc_cpu_reset(). QEMU 11 split the
old tb_flush() into a synchronous tb_flush__exclusive_or_serial() and an
asynchronous queue_tb_flush(); the latter only schedules the flush on the
CPU work queue (processed at the next cpu_loop_exit). With the async variant
the PPC can execute stale translation blocks left over from before the reset
before the queued flush runs, so WarpOS / AmigaOS 3.x boots to a black screen
(BlitterStudio/amiberry#2114) while AmigaOS 4 (different timing) survives.

Restore the synchronous flush. The reset path always runs with the PPC paused
or not yet started, i.e. the VM is not in RUN_STATE_RUNNING, which is exactly
when tb_flush__exclusive_or_serial() may be called directly. Fall back to the
async queue if a reset ever arrives while the VM is running.
---
 uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c | 19 ++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c
@@ -367,7 +367,25 @@
     uae_log("QEMU: NIP = 0x%08x\n", state.env->nip);
 
     uae_log("QEMU: Flushing all JIT translation blocks\n");
-    queue_tb_flush(CPU(state.cpu));
+    /*
+     * Frode's original qemu-uae plugin and the QEMU 9.2.4 build flush the
+     * translation block cache *synchronously* on reset. QEMU 11 split the old
+     * tb_flush() into a synchronous tb_flush__exclusive_or_serial() and an
+     * asynchronous queue_tb_flush(), the latter only scheduling the flush on
+     * the CPU work queue (processed at the next cpu_loop_exit). With the async
+     * variant the PPC can execute stale translation blocks left over from
+     * before the reset before the queued flush runs, so WarpOS / AmigaOS 3.x
+     * boots to a black screen (issue #2114). Restore the synchronous flush:
+     * the reset path always runs with the PPC paused / not yet started, i.e.
+     * the VM is not in RUN_STATE_RUNNING, which is exactly when
+     * tb_flush__exclusive_or_serial() is allowed to be called directly. Fall
+     * back to the async queue if a reset ever arrives while the VM is running.
+     */
+    if (!runstate_is_running()) {
+        tb_flush__exclusive_or_serial();
+    } else {
+        queue_tb_flush(CPU(state.cpu));
+    }
 }
 
 static uint32_t qemu_uae_get_cr(const CPUPPCState *env)
--
2.40.0
